@startuml testing-pyramid-diagram

title AI Trip Planner - Testing Pyramid Strategy

skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor LightBlue
    BorderColor Black
    FontSize 12
}

package "E2E Tests (5%)" #LightYellow {
}

package "          Integration Tests (15%)          " #LightGreen {
}

package "                    Unit Tests (80%)                    " #LightBlue {
}

note right of "E2E Tests (5%)"
  **End-to-End Testing**
  ----
  • Full user journey tests
  • Browser automation
  • API integration tests
  • Slowest, most expensive
  • Run before deployment
  
  **Execution Time:** 5-10 minutes
  **Examples:**
  • Complete trip planning flow
  • User submits request → receives itinerary
end note

note right of "          Integration Tests (15%)          "
  **Integration Testing**
  ----
  • API endpoint tests
  • Service interaction tests
  • Database integration
  • External API mocking
  • Medium speed
  
  **Execution Time:** 1-2 minutes
  **Examples:**
  • POST /api/plan-trip endpoint
  • Agent + Tool integration
  • External API responses
end note

note right of "                    Unit Tests (80%)                    "
  **Unit Testing**
  ----
  • Individual function tests
  • Component isolation
  • Fast execution
  • High coverage
  • Run on every commit
  
  **Execution Time:** 10-30 seconds
  **Examples:**
  • Agent reasoning logic
  • Tool functions (geocoding, weather)
  • Pydantic model validation
  • Helper utilities
end note

legend bottom
  **Testing Strategy Benefits:**
  
  1. **Fast Feedback** - Most tests run in seconds
  2. **Low Cost** - Unit tests are cheap to maintain
  3. **High Coverage** - 80% of code tested at unit level
  4. **Reliable** - Isolated tests = fewer flaky tests
  5. **Scalable** - Pyramid structure scales well
  
  **Test Distribution:**
  • Unit Tests: ~80 tests (80%)
  • Integration Tests: ~15 tests (15%)
  • E2E Tests: ~5 tests (5%)
  • Total: ~100 tests
endlegend

@enduml
